quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  10,26,Those who do good will have the finest reward¬†and ňĻevenňļ more.¬†Neither gloom nor disgrace will cover their faces. It is they who will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  10,27,"As for those who commit evil, the reward of an evil deed is its equivalent. Humiliation will cover them‚ÄĒwith no one to protect them from Allah‚ÄĒas if their faces were covered with patches of the night‚Äôs deep darkness. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  10,28,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day We will gather them all together then say to those who associated others ňĻwith Allah in worshipňļ, ‚ÄúStay in your places‚ÄĒyou and your associate-gods.‚ÄĚ We will separate them from each other, and their associate-gods will say, ‚ÄúIt was not us that you worshipped"
  10,29,Allah is sufficient as a Witness between each of us that we were totally unaware of your worship.‚ÄĚ
  10,30,Then and there every soul will face ňĻthe consequences ofňļ what it had done. They all will be returned to Allah‚ÄĒtheir True Master. And whatever ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them
  10,31,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho provides for you from heaven and earth? Who owns ňĻyourňļ hearing and sight? Who brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living? And who conducts every affair?‚ÄĚ They will ňĻsurelyňļ say, ‚ÄúAllah.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWill you not then fear ňĻHimňļ"
  10,32,That is Allah‚ÄĒyour True Lord. So what is beyond the truth except falsehood? How can you then be turned away?‚ÄĚ
  10,33,And so your Lord‚Äôs decree has been proven true against the rebellious‚ÄĒthat they will never believe
  10,34,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúCan any of your associate-gods originate creation and then resurrect it?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúňĻOnlyňļ Allah originates creation and then resurrects it. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  10,35,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúCan any of your associate-gods guide to the truth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúňĻOnlyňļ Allah guides to the truth.‚ÄĚ Who then is more worthy to be followed: the One Who guides to the truth or those who cannot find the way unless guided? What is the matter with you? How do you judge"
  10,36,Most of them follow nothing but ňĻinheritedňļ assumptions. ňĻAndňļ surely assumptions can in no way replace the truth. Allah is indeed All-Knowing of what they do
  10,37,"It is not ňĻpossibleňļ for this Quran to have been produced by anyone other than Allah. In fact, it is a confirmation of what came before, and an explanation of the Scripture. It is, without a doubt, from the Lord of all worlds"
  10,38,"Or do they claim, ‚ÄúHe¬†made it up!‚ÄĚ? Tell them ňĻO Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúProduce one s√Ľrah¬†like it then, and seek help from whoever you can‚ÄĒother than Allah‚ÄĒif what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  10,39,"In fact, they ňĻhastilyňļ rejected the Book without comprehending it and before the fulfilment of its warnings. Similarly, those before them were in denial. See then what was the end of the wrongdoers"
  10,40,Some of them will ňĻeventuallyňļ believe in it; others will not. And your Lord knows best the corruptors
  10,41,"If they deny you, then say, ‚ÄúMy deeds are mine and your deeds are yours. You are free of what I do and I am free of what you do!‚ÄĚ"
  10,42,"Some of them listen to what you say, but can you make the deaf hear even though they do not understand"
  10,43,"And some of them look at you, but can you guide the blind even though they cannot see"
  10,44,"Indeed, Allah does not wrong people in the least, but it is people who wrong themselves"
  10,45,"On the Day He will gather them, it will be as if they had not stayed ňĻin the worldňļ except for an hour of a day,¬†ňĻas though they were onlyňļ getting to know one another. Lost indeed will be those who denied the meeting with Allah, and were not ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  10,46,"Whether We show you ňĻO Prophetňļ some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die ňĻbefore thatňļ, to Us is their return and Allah is a Witness over what they do"
  10,47,"And for every community there is a messenger. After their messenger has come,¬†judgment is passed on them in all fairness, and they are not wronged"
  10,48,"They ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  10,49,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have no power to benefit or protect myself, except by the Will of Allah.‚ÄĚ For each community there is an appointed term. When their time arrives, they cannot delay it for a moment, nor could they advance it"
  10,50,"Tell them ňĻO Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if His torment were to overcome you by night or day‚ÄĒdo the wicked realize what they are ňĻreallyňļ asking Him to hasten"
  10,51,Will you believe in it only after it has overtaken you? Now? But you always wanted to hasten it!‚ÄĚ
  10,52,"Then the wrongdoers will be told, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of eternity! Are you not rewarded except for what you used to commit?‚ÄĚ"